<subSubSection id="C34665385B55A90D3BD83588FD27FCC5" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE336B35B55A90D3BD83588FD27FCC5" blockId="48.[151,1437,529,842]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B928EAA15B55A90D3BD83588FEBFFD36" bold="true" box="[199,315,673,698]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species could be distinguished from its congeners by: 1) body dark brown, with light brown antennae and legs; 2) punctures on pronotum larger than those on head; 3) admedian row consisting of 10–12 punctures; lateral row, curvedly arranged, of 14–18 punctures; 4) mesoscutellum covered with polygonal reticulum; 5) basal impression of tergites III–VII impunctate, but bearing distinct isodiameter mesh; 6) paired linear rows of black spines at side of inner sac.
</paragraph>
